# ORM Models General Standard

- Follow `docs/platforms/backend/patterns/orm-model-authoring-standard.md`.
- Start from `docs/platforms/backend/patterns/orm-constitution-map.md`.
- Keep Ejtmaa style only; do not import foreign project conventions.
- Require `Attrs` + `attributes()` + `initOptions()` + `boot()` + factory export pattern.
- Keep naming consistent: `XModel`, `modelName`, `tableName`, typed relation mixins.
- Ensure field parity between `Attrs` and `attributes()`, including virtual fields used by callers.
- Group Attrs with `//relations`, `//info`, `//virtual` comments; keep `attributes()` order aligned with that grouping.
- Add indexes/scopes only for actual query needs; no dead scopes.
- Keep helper methods deterministic, typed, and domain-focused.
- No resolver-only mutation security; requester/model contract remains source of truth.
- Before finalizing, pass `docs/platforms/backend/patterns/orm-model-compliance-checklists.md`.
